                                 AM Reprint Policy

@{U}                                                                           @{UU}

Because the Amiga community must have unity if it is to survive, it must be
able to share information throughout. Therefore, Excelsior Digital Publishing
grants general permission for material contained within The Amiga Monitor to
be reprinted in other publications. We ask that, if you choose to do so, you
fulfill several minor obligations:
@{LINDENT 4}

*  Please contact us via e-mail to MikeWebb@CompuServe.COM first.
*  Please include the name, position at AM, and e-mail address, if possible,
   of the original creator of the material being reprinted.
*  If possible, at least one of the following URL's should be included:
@{LINDENT 8}

*  http://ourworld.compuserve.com/HomePages/MikeWebb/
*  http://www.cucug.org/amiga/amiinfo/monitor/
@{LINDENT 4}

